Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.90,0:00:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,《纸牌屋》前情提要...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Previously on House of Cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.61,0:00:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我从来没有见过\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I have never known anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.36,0:00:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,比加勒特·沃克 更诚实  正直  爱国的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more honest, ethical and patriotic than Garrett Walker.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.74,0:00:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你居然算计我  弗兰克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You set me up, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.45,0:00:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,假如总统对我的指责\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's say that what the President has accused me of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.07,0:00:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,属实\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.58,0:00:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这就真的很糟吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Would that be so bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.87,0:00:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我的敌人想置我于死地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My enemies want me dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.21,0:00:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你这是逼我给他们证据\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're asking me to give them confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.00,0:00:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,作为回报  我们会给你提供避难所\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And we're giving you safe haven in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.42,0:00:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,机会只有一次  冯先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is a one-time offer, Mr. Feng.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.17,0:00:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我的客户要行使宪法第五修正案赋予的权利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My client exercises his right to plead the Fifth Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.13,0:00:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你是否曾用这些捐赠来换取政治利益\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Did you ever use these contributions to bargain for political favors?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我的客户要行使宪法第五修正案赋予的权利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My client exercises his right to plead the Fifth Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,发动不了吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Having trouble starting it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.68,0:00:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,她得离开\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}She needs to be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.77,0:00:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你不在乎她在不在这儿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But you said you didn't care if she was here...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我不需要解释什么\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I don't need to explain myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.35,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想让你待在这儿  好吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I don't want you here. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.31,0:00:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我不像你爱我那样爱着你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I don't love you the way that you love me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.48,0:00:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为不勇敢的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What I don't think is brave
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.03,0:00:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,是克莱尔·安德伍德逃避这场辩论\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is Claire Underwood dodging this debate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.24,0:00:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,找你替她进行这场斗争\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and having you fight this battle for her instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.36,0:00:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,其实我现在与她合作了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm actually working with her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.86,0:00:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我要撤销法案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm withdrawing the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.99,0:00:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,可她那样让我下不来台\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After what she did to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:00:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,也许杰姬·夏普说对了 你他妈就是个懦夫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe Jackie Sharp is right. You are a fucking coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.74,0:01:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,但他给我们开了处方药\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But he prescribed us medication.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.37,0:01:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你提过了  处方药的事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Have you mentioned it? The medication?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.41,0:01:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的总统正寻求心理治疗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our President is seeking psychological treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.38,0:01:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,并且向美国人民隐瞒这一点\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and chose to hide this from the American people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.04,0:01:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为我们众议院的同事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I believe our colleagues in the House
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.05,0:01:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,已经有足够理由考虑弹劾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}certainly have enough to consider Articles of Impeachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.05,0:01:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你要我做的  几乎是叛国\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What you're asking is just shy of treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.30,0:01:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.39,0:01:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是政治\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Which is politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.22,0:01:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的总统不仅服用精神药物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We have a president who not only took mind-altering medication --
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.72,0:01:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,当美国舰队与中国对峙时\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a man who has his finger on the button
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.86,0:01:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他可以随时批准实施打击\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}while U.S. Ships are squaring off with China --
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.31,0:01:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,还授意他的白宫顾问去干预...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but then instructed his White House counsel to coach a --
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.56,0:01:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,据称  先生  没有被证实\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Allegedly, sir. Not proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.39,0:01:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,去干预证人  他的做法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To coach a witness. Which is behavior either resulting
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.72,0:01:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,要么是受药物影响  要么更糟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the use of those drugs, or worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.32,0:01:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是有意想践踏法律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a deliberate attempt to obstruct the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.58,0:01:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你不觉得两种情况都该被弹劾吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now wouldn't you call either scenario impeachable?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.54,0:01:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,那该由国会决定  先生  而不是我\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's for the United States Congress to decide, sir. Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.11,0:01:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道总统在服用任何药物吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Were you aware that the president was taking any form of medication?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.14,0:01:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,不  我不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, I was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你注意到他举止古怪吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Did you notice him acting in a bizarre fashion?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.52,0:01:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-情绪不稳  语无伦次    -没有  先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- Unstable, incoherent?   - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.71,0:02:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,-有任何奇怪的行为吗    -没有  先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- Any odd behavior?   - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.05,0:02:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在贸易战之际解雇幕僚长不算吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not even firing his chief of staff in the midst of a trade war?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.33,0:02:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他没有解雇我  是我主动辞职的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He didn't fire me. I resigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你能告诉我们为什么吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Would you tell us why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.17,0:02:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我辞职是因为我觉得自己无法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I resigned because I felt I could no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.19,0:02:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,再以最好的状态为总统服务\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}serve the president to the best of my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.58,0:02:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,发生了什么变化  是什么让你得出那样的结论\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And what changed? How did you come to that conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我与白宫中的某些人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I had some fundamental differences of opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.09,0:02:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,基本理念不合\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with certain people in the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,比如谁  总统吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like who? The president?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.48,0:02:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不  先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.85,0:02:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,那某些人是指谁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, what certain people then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.23,0:02:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,实际上只有一个人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One person, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.46,0:02:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,副总统  弗兰克·安德伍德\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The vice president, Frank Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.89,0:02:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他想让你离开吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He wanted you gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.72,0:02:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我不敢说副总统想怎么样  不想怎么样\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can't speak as to what the vice president did or didn't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.80,0:02:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他想要隐藏什么吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Was he trying to hide anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.61,0:02:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他是不是怕你曝光什么\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Was he afraid you might expose something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.28,0:02:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,那你得去问他  先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You'd have to ask him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.10,0:02:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,司法委员会正在上演的是一出闹剧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's happening in the Judiciary Committee is a farce.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.96,0:02:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,共和党正在利用这种...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Republicans are exploiting the situ--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.69,0:02:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,插一句  副总统先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Excuse me, Mr. Vice President,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.74,0:02:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是共和党\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it's not just Republicans.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.87,0:02:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不少民主党人也站出来说\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A number of Democrats have come out saying
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.31,0:02:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他们支持弹劾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they would support impeachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:03:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,包括多数党党鞭  杰姬·夏普\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Including the Majority Whip, Jackie Sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,这令人发指\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Which is egregious,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.05,0:03:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,因为委员会还在进行听证\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}since the committee hasn't stopped hearing testimony,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.26,0:03:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,特别检查官也没有完成调查\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and nor has the special prosecutor completed her investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.33,0:03:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你极力维护总统\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You vigorously defend the president,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,但有报道称你们已经闹僵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but there are reports that you've had a falling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.73,0:03:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你们好几个星期没说过话了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That you haven't spoken in weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,一派胡言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That is simply not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.94,0:03:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我与白宫的高级官员通过话\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've spoken to senior staff at the White House
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.51,0:03:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他说总统担心你会在2016年大选中与他竞争\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who say the president is worried you want to run against him in 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.85,0:03:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,而就在今天  琳达·瓦斯奎兹暗指你...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And just today Linda Vasquez intimated that you --
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.46,0:03:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我相信总统一定会在2016年竞选连任\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Look, I fully expect that the president will run in 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.79,0:03:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我希望他能够慷慨地邀请我\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and I hope he's generous enough to invite me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.95,0:03:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,作他的竞选伙伴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to be his running mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.24,0:03:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,弹劾  定罪  如果是这个结果呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Impeachment, conviction. Let's say it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不会的  他完全是无辜的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It won't. He's completely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我们假设一下  你成了总统\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let's say it does happen. You become president.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.99,0:03:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会去想象那个情形\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That is not a scenario I'm going to entertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但你脑中肯定有过这个想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the thought must have crossed your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.14,0:03:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而且可以说  如果不是因为你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And one could make the argument that the president
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,总统也不会陷入这样的窘境\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wouldn't be in this predicament if it weren't for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.80,0:03:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是你的幕僚长与冯和拉尼根的牵连\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's your staff's involvement with Feng and Lanagin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,才引发了邓巴的调查\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that expanded Dunbar's investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.96,0:03:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这些弹劾听证\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Look, these impeachment hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.27,0:03:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}随之发现了出行记录\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which resulted in the travel logs --
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.20,0:03:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,是政治操纵的结果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are the result of political maneuvering,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.19,0:04:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-而不是    -是你在操纵还是共和党\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- not the fact that--   - Your maneuverings, or the Republicans?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.31,0:04:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,莫里  我一直很喜欢你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Morley, I've always liked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.50,0:04:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你的问题很尖锐\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You ask the tough questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.80,0:04:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你当然可以质疑我的判断\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And you can certainly question my judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.15,0:04:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,但不要质疑我的爱国心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But do not question my patriotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.67,0:04:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我为国家和总统服务  而不是我自己\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I serve this nation and my president, not myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.61,0:04:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他满口谎言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He's lying through his teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.82,0:04:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们所做的已经见效了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What we're doing is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,让大家一直私下谈论\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We keep the whisper campaign alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们让他显得渴望权利  显得奸诈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We spin him as power-hungry, as duplicitous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.55,0:04:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,将焦点集中在他身上  而不是你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Focus attention on him. Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.30,0:04:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,最新支持率是多少  20%吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What's the latest? 20%?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.97,0:04:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,佐格比的数据是24%  你的讲话起了作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Zogby has you at 24. Your speech made a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.31,0:04:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,支持率正在上升\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The approval numbers are moving in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.84,0:04:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能再这么小打小闹了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We need to do more than play the spin game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.12,0:04:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要打垮弗兰克  让他而不是我去当牺牲品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We need to destroy Frank. Offer his head instead of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.19,0:04:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-我们利用雷蒙德·塔斯克    -怎么利用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- We use Raymond Tusk.   - How?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的听证会上  在他去司法委员会时\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At his hearing. When he goes to the Judiciary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.24,0:04:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,先生  你已经被指控干预一个证人了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sir, you're already being accused of coaching one witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你再干预另一...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you take steps to coach anoth--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.54,0:04:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,不是干预  是让他说出事实\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not coaching. The truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.03,0:04:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,雷蒙德承认洗钱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Raymond admits to the money laundering,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.74,0:04:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,把弗兰克推到风口浪尖  说我什么都不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}puts Frank at the center of this, and says I knew nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,之后我们会回报他的诚实\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And then we'll reward him for his honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你是说特赦吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You mean a pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我想让你跟他去谈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want you to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.23,0:05:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,让我自己陷于危险之中吗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And put myself at risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.96,0:05:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在不在政府供职了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, you're not part of this administration anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.37,0:05:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,没有法律规定你不能去拜访雷蒙德·塔斯克\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no law that says you can't pay Raymond Tusk a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.68,0:05:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,作为回报  辞职也不非得永久有效  琳达\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And in return, resignations don't have to last forever, Linda.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.08,0:05:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我这么做  你得和我保持距离  越远越好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If I do this, you have to be a million miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.96,0:05:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,特莉莎和我会去戴维营\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tricia and I'll go to Camp David.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.84,0:05:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,不算特别远  但够了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not a million miles away, but it'll do the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以对琳达下手  调查她的过去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can go after Linda. Dig into her past --
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.28,0:05:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,搞定她解决不了大问题\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Neutralizing her won't neutralize the bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,是总统想要我的命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the president that's after blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,那他打算怎么做\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then what's his move?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.38,0:05:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他不能要求我辞职  只能把我挤走\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He can't ask me to resign. He'd have to force me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.26,0:05:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,要挤走我的话  如果我是他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And to do that, if I were him,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.57,0:05:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定会回去找最初成就我的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I would return to the hand that first fed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-雷蒙德·塔斯克吗    -没错\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- Raymond Tusk?   - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.68,0:06:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,不会  他要是把你卷进去  他自己也难保\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, he'd have to implicate himself to implicate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.10,0:06:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,除非他能得到赦免\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not if he gets a pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.06,0:06:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这是唯一只有总统才能开出的条件\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the one thing that only a president can offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.17,0:06:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,塔斯克是个手榴弹  如果他赦免了他...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tusk is a hand grenade. If he pardons him --
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.92,0:06:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,没错  塔斯克是个手榴弹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're right. Tusk is a hand grenade,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们得拽下保险栓  朝沃克扔过去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and we need to pull the pin and throw him at Walker
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,否则就是沃克拽下保险栓  扔向我们了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before Walker pulls the pin and throws him at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.08,0:06:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我得和雷蒙德见面  一对一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to meet with Raymond, one on one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我代表你去谈吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Let me speak on your behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.29,0:06:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,-这样的话  如果有人发现    -我了解雷蒙德\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- That way if anyone finds -- -I know Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.87,0:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他只会对我做出回应\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He won't respond to anyone but me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.01,0:06:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,他的听证会安排在什么时候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When's his hearing scheduled?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.24,0:06:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,后天下午两点\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh, day after tomorrow. Two p.m.
